1
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:10,961
♪Love's little quiz
takes seven parts sweet♪

2
00:00:10,962 --> 00:00:13,559
♪And three parts bitter,
till you and I meet♪

3
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:17,159
♪I pretend I'm not there,
but secretly stay♪

4
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:26,399
♪Waiting for you♪

5
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:31,400
♪We've got so many
romantic dreams to unfold♪

6
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:36,224
♪Finally hearing
the I love you I long to hold♪

7
00:00:36,225 --> 00:00:39,839
♪Falling fast
into the swirl of your eyes♪

8
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:42,399
♪It's just too tempting, so tempting♪

9
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:45,499
♪Never could I have guessed♪

10
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,499
♪My heart's rhythm♪

11
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,632
♪How beautiful it is, meeting you♪

12
00:01:02,975 --> 00:01:05,961
=Late to Love=
(Adapted from "My Husband Is A Billionaire!")

13
00:01:05,962 --> 00:01:09,107
=Episode 4=

14
00:01:19,712 --> 00:01:23,311
♪Sometimes we roll the dice♪

15
00:01:23,312 --> 00:01:27,098
,♪To see what the future hides♪

16
00:01:27,099 --> 00:01:31,579
♪Spinning us round and round
like a never-ending ride♪

17
00:01:31,580 --> 00:01:32,780
So?

18
00:01:34,940 --> 00:01:36,420
What do you think?

19
00:01:38,259 --> 00:01:39,299
Is your face

20
00:01:39,540 --> 00:01:40,900
a little

21
00:01:41,300 --> 00:01:42,500
asymmetrical?

22
00:01:44,580 --> 00:01:46,138
Here's a fun fact for you.

23
00:01:46,139 --> 00:01:48,459
No one's face is perfectly symmetrical.

24
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:50,220
I meant

25
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:52,260
your eye makeup.

26
00:01:54,619 --> 00:01:55,620
Is it?

27
00:01:59,100 --> 00:02:00,700
Oh, some touchups?

28
00:02:30,260 --> 00:02:31,539
Mr. Huo.

29
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:33,259
Mr. Huo. Mrs. Huo.

30
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:48,259
You must be Mrs. Huo.

31
00:02:48,260 --> 00:02:49,979
You really are young and beautiful.

32
00:02:49,980 --> 00:02:51,259
Mr. Huo sure is

33
00:02:51,260 --> 00:02:52,900
a lucky man.

34
00:02:54,219 --> 00:02:54,979
You flatter us.

35
00:02:54,980 --> 00:02:55,618
This is my wife.

36
00:02:55,619 --> 00:02:57,020
Hello, Mr. Wang.

37
00:02:58,339 --> 00:03:00,300
You know who I am?

38
00:03:00,580 --> 00:03:01,618
Of course.

39
00:03:01,619 --> 00:03:03,459
I often hear Beiyan mention you.

40
00:03:03,460 --> 00:03:04,618
The group's efficiency division

41
00:03:04,619 --> 00:03:06,378
has achieved today's success

42
00:03:06,379 --> 00:03:07,979
thanks to your years of leadership.

43
00:03:07,980 --> 00:03:09,938
Mr. Huo is usually so stern.

44
00:03:09,939 --> 00:03:13,060
I didn't expect him to praise me.

45
00:03:13,580 --> 00:03:14,819
Of course.

46
00:03:14,860 --> 00:03:15,938
What's going on?

47
00:03:15,939 --> 00:03:17,098
I have no idea.

48
00:03:17,099 --> 00:03:20,340
She probably read the company's profile
on the way here.

49
00:03:20,580 --> 00:03:21,818
The drive was only ten minutes.

50
00:03:21,819 --> 00:03:23,699
She memorized the whole thing?

51
00:03:24,779 --> 00:03:26,419
Ask her. Why are you asking me?

52
00:03:26,420 --> 00:03:27,180
How would I know?

53
00:03:27,499 --> 00:03:28,939
Is she that amazing?

54
00:03:30,740 --> 00:03:32,378
I just memorized it on the way here.

55
00:03:32,379 --> 00:03:33,859
Just like how people

56
00:03:33,860 --> 00:03:35,218
end up reading the shampoo labels

57
00:03:35,219 --> 00:03:36,139
in the bathroom

58
00:03:36,140 --> 00:03:37,459
if they forgot their phone.

59
00:03:37,460 --> 00:03:38,498
Curiosity for knowledge

60
00:03:38,499 --> 00:03:39,780
can help pass the time.

61
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:40,818
Do you do that?

62
00:03:40,819 --> 00:03:42,058
No. I don't.

63
00:03:42,059 --> 00:03:43,099
Me neither.

64
00:03:43,740 --> 00:03:44,740
Mrs. Huo,

65
00:03:45,219 --> 00:03:46,498
you must be very supportive

66
00:03:46,499 --> 00:03:47,498
of Beiyan's career,

67
00:03:47,499 --> 00:03:48,778
right?

68
00:03:48,779 --> 00:03:50,699
The group is expecting major changes.

69
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:53,459
Beiyan has decided to go back
into pharmaceutical business.

70
00:03:53,460 --> 00:03:54,938
But the water runs deep,

71
00:03:54,939 --> 00:03:56,020
and the risks are high.

72
00:03:56,219 --> 00:03:57,780
What do you think, Mrs. Huo?

73
00:03:58,779 --> 00:03:59,338
Nange and I...

74
00:03:59,339 --> 00:04:00,580
You're too kind, Mr. Li.

75
00:04:00,819 --> 00:04:01,938
Beiyan and the experts

76
00:04:01,939 --> 00:04:04,460
will weigh the group's strategy.

77
00:04:04,779 --> 00:04:07,460
Though I do know
a little about pharmaceuticals.

78
00:04:07,539 --> 00:04:10,179
The industry's landscape
has already changed.

79
00:04:10,180 --> 00:04:12,459
Small biotech companies
have made a huge impact

80
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:14,218
on traditional giants

81
00:04:14,219 --> 00:04:15,338
through cutting-edge

82
00:04:15,339 --> 00:04:17,059
innovative drug licensing partnerships.

83
00:04:17,219 --> 00:04:18,619
If Huo Group wants to break through,

84
00:04:18,620 --> 00:04:20,178
catching up alone isn't enough.

85
00:04:20,179 --> 00:04:22,538
Your insights into Huo Group

86
00:04:22,539 --> 00:04:25,659
have truly opened my eyes.

87
00:04:26,260 --> 00:04:27,460
Just some humble opinions.

88
00:04:29,659 --> 00:04:30,859
A toast to you.

89
00:04:30,979 --> 00:04:32,619
Here's to a successful partnership
tonight.

90
00:04:36,940 --> 00:04:38,820
When can we end this?

91
00:04:38,859 --> 00:04:39,778
I feel like this dress

92
00:04:39,779 --> 00:04:41,700
is about to crush my ribs.

93
00:04:41,940 --> 00:04:43,658
Hand in there a little longer.

94
00:04:43,659 --> 00:04:45,538
My dad's way too cunning.

95
00:04:45,539 --> 00:04:47,259
It'll be bad if we slip up later.

96
00:04:47,260 --> 00:04:48,059
What do you mean?

97
00:04:48,060 --> 00:04:49,340
Don't scare me.

98
00:04:51,419 --> 00:04:53,338
Mr. Huo.

99
00:04:53,339 --> 00:04:54,579
Hello, everyone.

100
00:04:54,580 --> 00:04:55,738
Congratulations, Mr. Huo.

101
00:04:55,739 --> 00:04:56,338
Congratulations.

102
00:04:56,339 --> 00:04:57,499
Congrats.

103
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:58,858
Congratulations.

104
00:04:58,859 --> 00:04:59,658
Good everyone,

105
00:04:59,659 --> 00:05:00,218
honored guests

106
00:05:00,219 --> 00:05:01,580
and directors.

107
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:04,379
My son, Beiyan, has always been
impulsive in everything he does.

108
00:05:04,380 --> 00:05:05,380
Well then.

109
00:05:05,700 --> 00:05:06,899
Let's have him tell us

110
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:08,059
how they fell in love.

111
00:05:08,060 --> 00:05:08,939
How about it?

112
00:05:08,940 --> 00:05:10,259
Sure.

113
00:05:10,260 --> 00:05:11,179
Beiyan!

114
00:05:11,299 --> 00:05:12,340
Beiyan.

115
00:05:14,140 --> 00:05:14,658
Hang on.

116
00:05:14,659 --> 00:05:15,338
What love story

117
00:05:15,339 --> 00:05:16,780
do we even have to tell?

118
00:05:17,219 --> 00:05:18,099
Make one up.

119
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:19,940
You do it.

120
00:05:20,060 --> 00:05:22,739
You were making things up
with my dad yesterday? You do it.

121
00:05:22,979 --> 00:05:24,579
That was different. I used a formula.

122
00:05:24,580 --> 00:05:27,259
I had a logical framework for it.
How am I supposed to apply that today?

123
00:05:27,260 --> 00:05:28,259
Just use another formula.

124
00:05:28,260 --> 00:05:29,459
How am I supposed to do that?

125
00:05:29,460 --> 00:05:31,940
I've been single since birth.
What formula do I have?

126
00:05:34,620 --> 00:05:35,538
Then

127
00:05:35,539 --> 00:05:36,778
I'll control the flow later.

128
00:05:36,779 --> 00:05:37,820
Just follow my lead.

129
00:05:38,219 --> 00:05:38,978
Be careful.

130
00:05:38,979 --> 00:05:40,299
Don't let anything slip.

131
00:05:40,787 --> 00:05:41,418
Beiyan!

132
00:05:41,419 --> 00:05:42,379
I'm here.

133
00:05:42,380 --> 00:05:43,499
Coming.

134
00:05:45,219 --> 00:05:46,260
Beiyan,

135
00:05:46,859 --> 00:05:48,858
hurry and tell everyone

136
00:05:48,859 --> 00:05:50,218
the juicy story

137
00:05:50,219 --> 00:05:51,379
of how you two

138
00:05:51,380 --> 00:05:52,299
fell in love.

139
00:05:52,380 --> 00:05:53,139
I want

140
00:05:53,140 --> 00:05:54,178
to be the first to hear it.

141
00:05:54,179 --> 00:05:55,580
That's right.

142
00:05:57,020 --> 00:05:58,619
Tell us, Beiyan.

143
00:05:58,620 --> 00:06:00,499
Since everyone here

144
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:01,658
is so interested

145
00:06:01,659 --> 00:06:02,858
in our love story,

146
00:06:02,859 --> 00:06:04,259
I'll tell everyone

147
00:06:04,260 --> 00:06:05,738
how Nange and I

148
00:06:05,739 --> 00:06:08,499
first met.

149
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:11,179
Sure.

150
00:06:11,419 --> 00:06:12,098
Tell us.

151
00:06:12,099 --> 00:06:13,460
It was on a sunny day

152
00:06:13,700 --> 00:06:16,059
after autumn.

153
00:06:16,779 --> 00:06:17,820
Sunny day.

154
00:06:18,739 --> 00:06:21,739
I ran into her outside the lab

155
00:06:22,299 --> 00:06:23,580
at Linhai Medical University.

156
00:06:38,580 --> 00:06:40,819
She was carrying a stack
of research papers and almost fell.

157
00:06:40,820 --> 00:06:41,859
Careful!

158
00:06:42,739 --> 00:06:45,099
I caught her in my arms.

159
00:06:50,460 --> 00:06:51,940
And then?

160
00:06:53,940 --> 00:06:55,778
What a cliche plot.

161
00:06:55,779 --> 00:06:58,340
It's making my toes curl.

162
00:06:59,099 --> 00:07:00,419
Right, Nange?

163
00:07:03,020 --> 00:07:03,979
Yeah.

164
00:07:05,060 --> 00:07:06,059
I was about

165
00:07:06,060 --> 00:07:07,858
to return

166
00:07:07,859 --> 00:07:09,499
the neuroanatomy atlas

167
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:11,218
and "The New Modern Medicine".

168
00:07:11,219 --> 00:07:12,859
What's that?

169
00:07:15,260 --> 00:07:16,140
My...

170
00:07:16,260 --> 00:07:18,299
No need to brag about your reading list.

171
00:07:20,260 --> 00:07:22,379
I just didn't expect

172
00:07:22,380 --> 00:07:23,778
the guy who caught me

173
00:07:23,779 --> 00:07:26,059
to turn out to be the trustee.

174
00:07:28,339 --> 00:07:28,939
Are you alright?

175
00:07:28,940 --> 00:07:30,380
I... I'm fine.

176
00:07:34,539 --> 00:07:35,686
I'm Huo Beiyan.

177
00:07:35,687 --> 00:07:39,170
(Huo Group, Huo Beiyan)

178
00:07:40,659 --> 00:07:42,179
You are...

179
00:07:44,140 --> 00:07:45,739
I also didn't expect

180
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:48,298
that the trustee came to campus

181
00:07:48,299 --> 00:07:51,099
just to borrow a meal card.

182
00:07:56,339 --> 00:07:57,778
Mr. Huo, what brings you to the campus

183
00:07:57,779 --> 00:07:59,179
on a weekend?

184
00:08:00,659 --> 00:08:03,179
Since fate brought us together,
I'll just be direct.

185
00:08:03,460 --> 00:08:04,580
Can you

186
00:08:04,620 --> 00:08:06,619
lend me your meal card?

187
00:08:06,940 --> 00:08:08,340
Meal card?

188
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:09,858
Yes. Meal card.

189
00:08:09,859 --> 00:08:11,059
Meal card?

190
00:08:11,060 --> 00:08:12,419
I didn't expect that.

191
00:08:13,140 --> 00:08:14,338
This is too funny.

192
00:08:14,339 --> 00:08:15,019
Meal card?

193
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:16,418
Am I that hungry?

194
00:08:16,419 --> 00:08:17,820
Right, Beiyan?

195
00:08:18,859 --> 00:08:20,538
Y... Yeah. Exactly.

196
00:08:20,539 --> 00:08:21,580
Here's the thing.

197
00:08:22,419 --> 00:08:23,819
Actually before that,

198
00:08:23,820 --> 00:08:26,940
we met once
in the university's cafeteria.

199
00:08:30,260 --> 00:08:32,140
When I saw her then,

200
00:08:32,699 --> 00:08:33,619
my heart instantly

201
00:08:33,620 --> 00:08:36,538
skipped a beat for her.

202
00:08:36,539 --> 00:08:38,859
So to see her again,

203
00:08:38,860 --> 00:08:39,778
I kept

204
00:08:39,779 --> 00:08:42,859
wandering around the university lab.

205
00:08:43,860 --> 00:08:45,578
And I really did meet her again.

206
00:08:45,579 --> 00:08:46,979
I guess

207
00:08:46,980 --> 00:08:49,139
it was fated.

208
00:08:52,539 --> 00:08:53,339
Not bad.

209
00:08:53,340 --> 00:08:55,099
You patched the story back together.

210
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:58,940
And after that,

211
00:08:59,340 --> 00:09:01,499
Nange and I gradually got closer.

212
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:03,099
She may usually

213
00:09:03,220 --> 00:09:04,899
seem gentle and adorable,

214
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:07,540
but in private, she likes...

215
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:10,779
to play Monopoly.

216
00:09:11,260 --> 00:09:12,058
Monopoly?

217
00:09:12,059 --> 00:09:13,619
- Didn't see that coming.
- Monopoly?

218
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:16,259
I just happen to know a thing about it,

219
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:17,940
so it became one

220
00:09:18,179 --> 00:09:19,139
of the ways

221
00:09:19,140 --> 00:09:21,660
we spent time together.

222
00:09:27,020 --> 00:09:28,379
Huo Beiyan,

223
00:09:28,419 --> 00:09:30,859
let's settle this once
and for all today.

224
00:09:31,620 --> 00:09:32,739
Xu Nange,

225
00:09:33,020 --> 00:09:34,058
today

226
00:09:34,059 --> 00:09:36,820
I'll make you admit defeat.

227
00:09:41,140 --> 00:09:42,019
Yes.

228
00:09:42,020 --> 00:09:44,139
I'm from a science
and engineering background.

229
00:09:44,140 --> 00:09:45,979
My fascination with probability

230
00:09:45,980 --> 00:09:48,940
made me absolutely obsessed
with the game.

231
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,139
But I didn't expect

232
00:09:53,140 --> 00:09:54,538
the university trustee

233
00:09:54,539 --> 00:09:57,418
to use underhanded tricks

234
00:09:57,419 --> 00:10:00,420
and cheat during the game.

235
00:10:01,260 --> 00:10:02,899
Cheat?

236
00:10:03,020 --> 00:10:04,660
He shouldn't have done that.

237
00:10:05,900 --> 00:10:06,899
Ms. Xu,

238
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:08,219
don't push it.

239
00:10:08,220 --> 00:10:10,339
You started it first.

240
00:10:10,340 --> 00:10:12,418
We're doomed if this falls apart.

241
00:10:12,419 --> 00:10:13,940
I'm not scared.

242
00:10:31,779 --> 00:10:32,458
Nange.

243
00:10:32,459 --> 00:10:33,700
Zichen's back.

244
00:10:33,939 --> 00:10:35,019
Boy.

245
00:10:35,059 --> 00:10:37,180
You just got back
and already causing a scene.

246
00:10:38,779 --> 00:10:39,538
Zichen's back.

247
00:10:39,539 --> 00:10:40,940
He just got back.

248
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:45,019
You got back earlier

249
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:46,859
without telling me.

250
00:10:47,020 --> 00:10:48,460
I wanted to give you...

251
00:10:48,939 --> 00:10:50,779
and her a surprise.

252
00:10:52,939 --> 00:10:54,300
Too bad it shattered.

253
00:11:10,340 --> 00:11:12,019
Apologies, everyone.

254
00:11:12,340 --> 00:11:14,499
I was in a hurry
to give Beiyan a surprise.

255
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:15,538
I didn't mean

256
00:11:15,539 --> 00:11:17,060
to ruin the mood.

257
00:11:17,179 --> 00:11:19,340
I'm sorry for the shock.

258
00:11:20,340 --> 00:11:21,259
Don't stop the music.

259
00:11:21,260 --> 00:11:22,178
Carry on.

260
00:11:22,179 --> 00:11:22,979
Alright.

261
00:11:22,980 --> 00:11:24,058
Come on.

262
00:11:24,059 --> 00:11:25,099
Let's continue.

263
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:28,979
Zichen,

264
00:11:28,980 --> 00:11:30,058
I only realized something

265
00:11:30,059 --> 00:11:31,820
recently myself.

266
00:11:33,779 --> 00:11:35,540
I want to talk to her first.

267
00:11:41,762 --> 00:11:48,036
♪All of my dreams, leading me here♪

268
00:11:48,037 --> 00:11:54,270
♪Fueling the fire
that help me fight all the fear♪

269
00:12:09,025 --> 00:12:12,799
♪What destiny brought us to meet♪

270
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:16,120
♪Two different worlds, a love so sweet♪

271
00:12:16,125 --> 00:12:19,499
♪A wish we made
in a past life, it seems♪

272
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:22,354
♪Destined to cross time and dream ♪

273
00:12:22,355 --> 00:12:26,195
♪Like a fairytale story told♪

274
00:12:26,275 --> 00:12:29,532
♪A gentle breeze feels so bold♪

275
00:12:29,550 --> 00:12:33,236
♪As your hair brushes past your ear♪

276
00:12:33,237 --> 00:12:35,594
♪I long to kiss your cheek, my dear♪

277
00:12:35,595 --> 00:12:39,834
♪All my longing, all my love for you♪

278
00:12:39,835 --> 00:12:42,395
♪Has never changed, it's forever true♪

279
00:12:42,837 --> 00:12:49,235
♪It's the hand of fate
that we meet again♪

280
00:12:50,037 --> 00:12:54,475
♪Let me hold you once again♪

281
00:12:54,725 --> 00:12:57,645
♪Resting against your chest♪

282
00:12:57,995 --> 00:13:03,236
♪Your warmth shines like stars at night♪

283
00:13:03,237 --> 00:13:08,036
♪Let me kiss you once again♪

284
00:13:08,037 --> 00:13:10,836
♪No reason needed♪

285
00:13:10,837 --> 00:13:13,034
♪My heart belongs to you♪

286
00:13:13,035 --> 00:13:18,755
♪I'm not afraid
to cross time to find you♪

